 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrindel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grindel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/02 7:05:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/grindel/elminster.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ST</span><hr size=1> Some clarification and background from someone who has an actual stake in this stuff.<br>
<br>
TMC and IC used to be very closely tied together.  TMC was originally a GM guild.  GMs from other servers created and ran the guild, until someone eventually got in trouble and they went underground for a while.  Some TMC members joined IC from what I understand.  Well recently the guild came back and in the meantime relations between the two groups soured for some reason I'm not privy to and really don't care to know about.<br>
<br>
Two days back IC and TMC had a staredown over the AC burrower.  As per the norm, IC won the staredown and took the burrower.  Later on, one of IC's more belligerent and charismatic leaders, a guy named Bakk, motivated his guild to take down the first warder to punish TMC, since they were just starting to farm ST.<br>
<br>
The reasoning here is pretty easy.  You can get primal weapons off of golems in ST, but the warders each dropped a bunch, guaranteed, every time they were killed.  Pulling a number directly from my behind, getting primal gear for your guild ups your dps by 20% or more, making encounters like AoW and other similar mobs much more feasible.<br>
<br>
There are 3 'big' guilds on Xegony; IC, my guild Havenlight, and the IS/VS/SOA consortium everyone calls Xegony Alliance 2 (XA2).  Lately, a few second tier guilds have become powerful enough to tackle encounters that previously the Big 3 squabbled over.  IC made a very calculated and tactical decision to slow these second tier guilds down in their advancement, keeping them from breathing down other guilds' necks on bigger game.<br>
<br>
I'd be a hypocrite if I said I was totally against this.  In fact, I'd suggested several times myself that HL release the sleeper.  We were the first guild to take down Warder 4 on our server, so we did feel a sense of entitlement.  But we were split 50-50, with a bunch of people not wanting to score the bad rep releasing him would cause.<br>
<br>
But recognize something.  People have actually been farming SoDs on Xegony for cash.  Player auctions right now has an SoD going for $1,250 in real money.  Imagine how things would get once three or four second tier guilds have the capacity to get SoDs, bumping up against the ebay farmers.  Talk about a riot ready to happen.<br>
<br>
So I'm torn a bit.  I truly feel bad for some of my friends in Jade Dragon, Undaunted, for some of HL's newer members and the like who won't be able to challenge themselves against the warders.  I'm sure they're just like I was; I could have cared less about the loot, I went there for the challenge of measuring myself against the warders.  I also feel a tiny bit bad that warders are off the table for a raid destination, even though we haven't been to ST for months.  But from a guild perspective it made logical sense for IC to do what they did.  Using the AC burrower incident as a catalyst is kind of lame, but the end result is something that probably needed to happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/02 7:05:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/aidon60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ST</span><hr size=1> On Karana, there is an agreement in place on the Council of Guilds to keep the 1st warder perma-alive.  Any guild who kills the 1st warder (thus waking the sleeper) would be considered a rogue guild and proceed to have every guild on the server leapfrogging them, lagging them out, blowing their spawns, and generally making their lives miserable =D<br>
<br>
There is absolutely no reason to wake the sleeper.  Farm what you need from ST, then move on and let the other folks have their shot. <p><p><center><img src=http://lilyanaeq.homestead.com/files/Signatures/Aidon.jpg>
