<br>
Cut and pasted my input on that thread below in response to people saying waking Sleeper serves no purpose.<br>
<br>
The reasoning behind releasing the Sleeper was to halt up and coming guilds total damage-output by denying them SoDs - which allows all of your guild to increase their dps due to the warrior aggro-curve being much steeper - and of course primals which in Velious played a huge part, I've seen numbers ranging from 10-20% damage increase from the added ATK.<br>
<br>
I'm willing to bet that this is the reasoning behind releasing him on 9 out of 10 servers once the effects were known after BoTS released him serverwide first.<br>
<br>
With Luclin out and the easy access to good taunting weapons - at least better than ToVN and very close to the SoDs effectiveness, this reasoning doesn't really hold true anymore and guilds loose the incentive to release the sleeper because it does makes them look bad too, and it doesn't really have the server-altering effect it did before Luclin.<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm just cynical, but I'm very sure this was the reasoning behind releasing him on Tribunal, and if our competing alliance of guilds hadn't released him, I'm sure we would have considered it once up and coming guilds were close to getting 20 people into ST.<br>
<br>
Releasing him does have its upsides for the server too, the servers top tier guilds (that has been in ST since warders) all but totally lost interest in First Brood dragons, letting the next tier of guilds have access to more dragon-loot and of course ST keys, letting them acquire some primal at a slower pace - if the warders had been there I'm sure there would have been more competition for ST keys on servers where he is awoken than there is now - so the pace may not be so much slower than it would have been. At least this is what happened on Tribunal .<br>
<br>
